---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Cta from '../../components/Cta.astro';
import { withBase } from '../../data/site';
---
<Base title="Director's Welcome — Eight Hands Martial Arts Academy">
  <PageHeader eyebrow="About" title="Director's Welcome" />
  <section class="bg-stone">
    <div class="container-content py-section-sm lg:py-section grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.6fr] gap-12 items-start">
      <img src={withBase('/img/kasemir-portrait.jpg')} alt="Dr. Kasemir, Director" loading="lazy" class="aspect-[3/4] reveal w-full h-full object-cover" />
      <div class="reveal space-y-5 text-lg text-slate/90">
        <p class="font-display text-2xl text-navy italic">Welcome to the Qi-House.</p>
        <p>Eight Hands Martial Arts Academy was founded on a simple belief: the most important lessons a person learns are not merely what to think or what to do, but how to govern themselves. While martial arts provide the vehicle, our purpose is much broader. We help students develop the confidence to act, the discipline to follow through, the focus to remain present, and the awareness to make thoughtful decisions under pressure.</p>
        <p>Every student arrives with a unique background, set of experiences, and personal goals. Some seek self-defense, others leadership, confidence, fitness, or personal growth. Regardless of where they begin, students are encouraged to take an active role in their own development. Through individualized instruction, guided practice, and meaningful challenge, they learn to communicate effectively, take responsibility for their choices, and contribute positively to the people around them.</p>
        <p>The culture of our academy is built upon participation. Growth is not something that happens to a student; it is something they help create through consistent effort, curiosity, and engagement. We believe that real development occurs when individuals are supported, challenged, and given opportunities to apply what they learn in practical ways. In this environment, confidence becomes earned, resilience becomes practiced, and leadership becomes a natural extension of personal responsibility.</p>
        <p>Whether you are a parent seeking meaningful opportunities for your child, or an adult looking to continue your own development, we invite you to explore what makes Eight Hands unique. Our goal is not simply to teach martial arts, but to help individuals build the habits, character, and capabilities that serve them throughout life.</p>
        <p class="font-display text-xl text-navy italic">At its heart, Eight Hands is a martial arts education in self-governance.</p>
        <div class="border-t border-navy/10 pt-5">
          <p class="font-display text-xl text-navy italic">Dr. Kasemir, Kyoshi</p>
          <p class="eyebrow !text-slate-400 mt-1">Director</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-0.5">Head Instructor · Eight Hands Martial Arts Academy</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Cta />
</Base>
